<article class="chapter">
  <a name="//apple_ref/doc/uid/TP40016784-CH9"></a><a name="//apple_ref/doc/uid/TP40016784-CH9-SW1"></a>
      <a name="//apple_ref/doc/uid/TP40016784-CH5"></a><a name="//apple_ref/doc/uid/TP40016784-CH5-SW1"></a>

  <h2 class='chapter-name'>Article Layout and Design</h2>


  
  	<section class="section">
  		<p class="para">
  With Apple News Format, you can create signature content for News. Beautiful typography, rich photo galleries, videos, and fun animations bring your articles to life. You can author once and News will optimize your content for iPhone, iPad, and iPad Pro, so your readers will have a great experience no matter which device theyâ€™re using.
</p>
<p class="para">
  This document covers some of the basic layout and design features for articles. All features covered in this document are included in downloadable JavaScript Object Notation (JSON) files. You can use the JSON examples to create your own designs.
</p>

		</section> 


  <section class="section">
  <a name="//apple_ref/doc/uid/TP40016784-CH9-SW3"></a>
  <h3 class="section-name" tabindex="0">Basic Design Features</h3>
  <p class="para">
  This section shows the some of the features covered in this primer for a basic example JSON article. The layout shows the scaling of an article on three different divices, using the iPad Pro, iPad, and iPhone.
</p><p class="para">
  <strong>First Screen</strong>
</p><figure class="figure">
  
  <span class="caption"></span>
  <img src="Art/anatomy1.jpeg" alt="image: ../Art/anatomy1.jpeg" width="700" height="394" />
</figure><p class="para">
  <strong>Second Screen</strong>
</p><figure class="figure">
  
  <span class="caption"></span>
  <img src="Art/anatomy2.jpg" alt="image: ../Art/anatomy2.jpg" width="700" height="394" />
</figure><p class="para">
  <strong>Third Screen</strong>
</p><figure class="figure">
  
  <span class="caption"></span>
  <img src="Art/anatomy3.jpeg" alt="image: ../Art/anatomy3.jpeg" width="700" height="394" />
</figure>
  
</section>
<section class="section">
  <a name="//apple_ref/doc/uid/TP40016784-CH9-SW2"></a>
  <h3 class="section-name" tabindex="0">How to Use This Primer</h3>
  <p class="para">
  This primer has six major sections grouped into categories of similar features. 
</p><ul class="list-bullet">
  <li class="item"><p class="para">
  <span class="x-name"><a href="TheBasicStructureofanArticle.html#//apple_ref/doc/uid/TP40016784-CH6-SW1" data-renderer-version="2" data-id="//apple_ref/doc/uid/TP40016784-CH6-SW1">Getting Started</a></span> covers the basic JSON structure.
</p>
</li><li class="item"><p class="para">
  <span class="x-name"><a href="AboutComponentContents.html#//apple_ref/doc/uid/TP40016784-CH33-SW1" data-renderer-version="2" data-id="//apple_ref/doc/uid/TP40016784-CH33-SW1">Using Components</a></span> explains how to design the layout and use text and style components.
</p>
</li><li class="item"><p class="para">
  <span class="x-name"><a href="ThePhotoComponent.html#//apple_ref/doc/uid/TP40016784-CH14-SW1" data-renderer-version="2" data-id="//apple_ref/doc/uid/TP40016784-CH14-SW1">Adding Imagery</a></span> discusses the photo component and the use of captions.
</p>
</li><li class="item"><p class="para">
  <span class="x-name"><a href="UsingaPullQuote.html#//apple_ref/doc/uid/TP40016784-CH23-SW1" data-renderer-version="2" data-id="//apple_ref/doc/uid/TP40016784-CH23-SW1">Using Quotes</a></span> shows you how to use pull quotes and ways you can style quotes.
</p>
</li><li class="item"><p class="para">
  <span class="x-name"><a href="UsingtheGalleryComponent.html#//apple_ref/doc/uid/TP40016784-CH25-SW1" data-renderer-version="2" data-id="//apple_ref/doc/uid/TP40016784-CH25-SW1">Selecting a Gallery</a></span> shows you how to include a sequence of images to enhance your articles.
</p>
</li><li class="item"><p class="para">
  <span class="x-name"><a href="Tweets.html#//apple_ref/doc/uid/TP40016784-CH30-SW1" data-renderer-version="2" data-id="//apple_ref/doc/uid/TP40016784-CH30-SW1">Using Embeds</a></span> explains how to insert maps and content from social media.
</p>
</li>
</ul><p class="para">
  Each section builds on the previous, providing code snippets for each feature. The snippets are followed by a downloadable <code class="code-voice">article.JSON</code> file containing all features discussed in the previous section(s). Each major section contains a set downloadble JSON files that include code for the entire section. Just navigate to the folder and select the file you want to work with. Each file contains the name of the design feature. 
</p><p class="para">
  The final chapter, <span class="x-name"><a href="TheJSON.html#//apple_ref/doc/uid/TP40016784-CH18-SW1" data-renderer-version="2" data-id="//apple_ref/doc/uid/TP40016784-CH18-SW1">Putting It Together</a></span>, contains the complete <code class="code-voice">article.JSON</code> example. You can use any of these files as templates and customize them for your needs.
</p>
  
</section>
<section class="section">
  <a name="//apple_ref/doc/uid/TP40016784-CH9-SW4"></a>
  <h3 class="section-name" tabindex="0">Related Documentation</h3>
  <p class="para">
  For additional information on JSON and Apple News Format, see <a href="https://developer.apple.com/library/ios/documentation/General/Conceptual/Apple_News_Format_Ref/">Apple News Format Reference</a>.
</p>
  
</section>

  	
